WEBVTT

00:00:20.375 --> 00:00:23.461
How have you been, Eun-ho?

00:00:25.547 --> 00:00:29.384
After graduating, I started a company
with my college friends.

00:00:32.720 --> 00:00:34.389
Do you still do kumdo?

00:00:36.266 --> 00:00:38.017
I quit after getting crushed by you.

00:00:41.396 --> 00:00:42.981
I should've gone easy on you.

00:00:52.949 --> 00:00:54.868
I struggled a lot after you dropped out.

00:00:56.703 --> 00:00:57.537
Dropped out?

00:00:58.705 --> 00:00:59.664
What happened?

00:01:02.208 --> 00:01:03.793
So that's the backstory, huh?

00:01:04.294 --> 00:01:05.128
Well…

00:01:09.215 --> 00:01:10.884
I had my reasons.

00:01:13.094 --> 00:01:14.762
You could've at least kept in touch.

00:01:15.972 --> 00:01:16.806
I'm sorry.

00:01:20.518 --> 00:01:22.312
So? What have you been up to?

00:01:24.314 --> 00:01:27.150
I'm a webtoon producer.

00:01:29.944 --> 00:01:30.862
WEBTOON PD

00:01:31.446 --> 00:01:32.447
A business card?

00:01:33.823 --> 00:01:36.492
I work at a company called Naemo,
near Hapjeong.

00:01:37.785 --> 00:01:38.786
That's so cool.

00:01:40.121 --> 00:01:40.997
It suits you.

00:01:42.457 --> 00:01:44.042
Here's my card.

00:01:48.171 --> 00:01:50.590
Producer Seo Mi-rae.

00:01:52.050 --> 00:01:53.051
For the first time,

00:01:53.134 --> 00:01:56.054
I'm the same person here
as I am in reality.

00:01:59.057 --> 00:02:02.852
It feels weird to hear you call me that.

00:02:20.912 --> 00:02:21.746
We're here.

00:02:21.829 --> 00:02:22.997
This is the place.

00:02:25.333 --> 00:02:27.126
So this is your company.

00:02:31.881 --> 00:02:33.424
Let's meet more often from now on.

00:02:35.218 --> 00:02:36.052
Okay.

00:02:36.135 --> 00:02:37.971
I can take you home. Where do you live?

00:02:38.471 --> 00:02:40.723
It's okay. You must be busy, so get going.

00:02:41.724 --> 00:02:42.558
It's dark out.

00:02:43.601 --> 00:02:47.313
I'm not 20 anymore.
I even drink soju at a pocha by myself.

00:02:48.940 --> 00:02:51.484
Even in college,
you never drank like most 20-year-olds.

00:02:55.280 --> 00:02:56.739
Anyway, I'll get going.

00:02:57.240 --> 00:02:58.074
See you soon.

00:03:43.745 --> 00:03:44.746
Hello?

00:03:45.246 --> 00:03:46.205
Hello?

00:03:47.332 --> 00:03:48.333
Hello?

00:03:48.833 --> 00:03:49.959
Did you make it home?

00:03:50.460 --> 00:03:52.670
I wanted to make sure you got back safely.

00:03:55.006 --> 00:03:55.965
Eun-ho?

00:03:56.549 --> 00:03:58.551
What is this? How is he calling me?

00:03:59.052 --> 00:03:59.886
Hello?

00:03:59.969 --> 00:04:02.472
Oh, yes. Just a moment.

00:04:09.145 --> 00:04:11.314
All subscribers
with a basic plan and above

00:04:11.397 --> 00:04:16.194
can send and receive calls and messages
with the characters after logging out.

00:04:16.277 --> 00:04:17.403
That's crazy!

00:04:17.487 --> 00:04:19.781
Hello? Isn't this Seo Mi-rae's phone?

00:04:20.531 --> 00:04:22.033
Oh, yes, Eun-ho.

00:04:22.116 --> 00:04:24.911
What are you up to?
I'm having trouble falling asleep.

00:04:25.995 --> 00:04:27.789
I'm also wide awake now.

00:04:28.289 --> 00:04:31.125
Then shall we talk until you get sleepy?

00:04:31.876 --> 00:04:32.835
Shall we?

00:04:34.962 --> 00:04:36.756
I've never met anyone who knows it.

00:04:36.839 --> 00:04:38.716
Any horror fan would know that film.

00:04:38.800 --> 00:04:41.094
The protagonist, being a villager,
was a fun choice.

00:04:41.177 --> 00:04:42.011
Right?

00:04:42.095 --> 00:04:46.474
Most folk horror films would go with
an outsider who's just arrived.

00:04:46.974 --> 00:04:47.809
Exactly!

00:04:48.476 --> 00:04:51.270
Want to watch a movie together next time?

00:04:52.438 --> 00:04:53.689
-A movie?
-Yeah.

00:04:53.773 --> 00:04:57.026
Let's meet near your office.
I'll come to Hapjeong Station.

00:04:57.110 --> 00:04:57.944
What?

00:04:59.070 --> 00:05:00.655
Are you uncomfortable with that?

00:05:03.116 --> 00:05:04.283
No, that's not…

00:05:11.416 --> 00:05:15.920
If you're okay with it, I can head over
around the time you get off work tomorrow.

00:05:26.848 --> 00:05:28.766
The realism is breathtaking.

00:05:29.350 --> 00:05:30.393
Sounds good.

00:05:31.644 --> 00:05:32.520
Then…

00:05:33.479 --> 00:05:34.605
I'll see you tomorrow.

00:05:40.903 --> 00:05:46.659
EPISODE 5
THE CAVEATS OF PERFECTION

00:05:53.708 --> 00:05:55.376
Sorry I'm late.

00:05:55.460 --> 00:05:57.128
Let me go grab some coffee.

00:05:57.211 --> 00:05:58.296
I already made some.

00:05:58.379 --> 00:06:00.381
It's cold, though, since you're late.

00:06:01.507 --> 00:06:02.675
Thank you.

00:06:03.176 --> 00:06:06.262
I was reviewing a submitted file
and lost track of time.

00:06:06.345 --> 00:06:07.346
Shall we get started?

00:06:09.140 --> 00:06:12.643
I didn't like this piece that much.
It was too imitative of existing works.

00:06:13.394 --> 00:06:14.479
Me too.

00:06:14.562 --> 00:06:16.564
Is anything ever completely original?

00:06:17.273 --> 00:06:19.442
The lines and page layouts
are too amateurish.

00:06:19.525 --> 00:06:21.444
Which can be fixed with our help.

00:06:22.320 --> 00:06:24.697
Do you think you can also fix
such a childish plot?

00:06:24.780 --> 00:06:27.909
Some titles top the charts
despite having a childish plot, you know.

00:06:34.207 --> 00:06:35.041
What?

00:06:36.083 --> 00:06:37.668
No, I just…

00:06:38.628 --> 00:06:40.963
Which titles might you be referring to?

00:06:41.047 --> 00:06:42.798
There are plenty of them, as you know.

00:06:45.134 --> 00:06:47.220
You're right. There are plenty.

00:06:49.847 --> 00:06:51.682
What's his problem today?

00:06:53.100 --> 00:06:54.268
Let's take a break.

00:07:09.867 --> 00:07:12.870
Did you get to work okay? Good luck today!

00:07:13.621 --> 00:07:17.124
When was the last time I received a text
from a guy checking in on me?

00:07:23.005 --> 00:07:25.174
Heading out for lunch? Let me come with.

00:07:25.800 --> 00:07:28.594
I have a lunch meeting.
Why don't you eat with Kyeong-nam?

00:07:28.678 --> 00:07:29.595
Shall we?

00:07:30.930 --> 00:07:32.181
We also have plans.

00:07:32.265 --> 00:07:33.683
Enjoy your meal.

00:07:35.977 --> 00:07:36.811
Let's go.

00:07:37.311 --> 00:07:38.145
Sure.

00:07:59.875 --> 00:08:01.419
This is so awkward.

00:08:03.838 --> 00:08:04.839
Do you like romance?

00:08:05.923 --> 00:08:06.757
What?

00:08:06.841 --> 00:08:08.968
I'm asking
because we'll be judging together.

00:08:10.803 --> 00:08:12.847
No. I don't like it.

00:08:13.472 --> 00:08:14.307
Me neither.

00:08:15.266 --> 00:08:16.392
So what?

00:08:18.811 --> 00:08:19.812
So what do you like?

00:08:22.315 --> 00:08:23.274
Horror.

00:08:23.941 --> 00:08:24.775
Why is that?

00:08:26.444 --> 00:08:28.279
Well, it's just…

00:08:28.362 --> 00:08:32.908
I barely notice my heart most of the time,
so I like the way they make it race.

00:08:34.076 --> 00:08:35.745
I also like horror. A lot.

00:08:35.828 --> 00:08:37.663
Who asked you?

00:08:40.499 --> 00:08:42.918
It must be hard for you
to work on The Man to Know.

00:08:44.128 --> 00:08:45.838
Yeah, I guess.

00:08:46.339 --> 00:08:48.257
I only got assigned that job
thanks to you.

00:08:49.342 --> 00:08:50.176
Hang in there.

00:09:06.025 --> 00:09:07.943
I'll be there soon.

00:09:10.112 --> 00:09:12.365
Take your time, and don't trip.

00:09:22.833 --> 00:09:23.668
Eun-ho!

00:09:28.964 --> 00:09:30.549
-Am I late?
-No.

00:09:31.509 --> 00:09:33.135
The movie is about to start. Let's go.

00:09:39.558 --> 00:09:40.851
Don't kill me!

00:09:46.816 --> 00:09:48.150
Don't kill me…

00:09:50.361 --> 00:09:52.405
Please don't kill me!

00:09:53.072 --> 00:09:54.824
Please don't kill me…

00:10:19.598 --> 00:10:21.058
Want some popcorn?

00:10:34.155 --> 00:10:37.616
What was it they said? That excitement
is not an emotion but a sensation?

00:10:40.077 --> 00:10:41.078
It's so sweet.

00:10:45.583 --> 00:10:46.751
A bit messy, isn't it?

00:10:49.378 --> 00:10:50.796
It's really nice in here.

00:10:51.297 --> 00:10:52.715
Everyone is out of the office.

00:10:53.299 --> 00:10:55.384
Take a look around. I'll get you a drink.

00:11:14.320 --> 00:11:15.488
I miss everyone.

00:11:21.535 --> 00:11:23.621
Looking back now, we were really young.

00:11:25.664 --> 00:11:26.791
I didn't know back then…

00:11:31.128 --> 00:11:32.713
that I'd never…

00:11:34.715 --> 00:11:36.133
forget about you.

00:11:43.641 --> 00:11:46.310
We have a nice rooftop.
Want to get some fresh air?

00:11:57.822 --> 00:11:58.656
What is it?

00:12:34.692 --> 00:12:36.193
Are you going to disappear again?

00:12:41.156 --> 00:12:41.991
No.

00:12:47.454 --> 00:12:49.915
I'm not going anywhere.

00:13:01.760 --> 00:13:04.638
On my way to work. Have a nice day.

00:13:11.478 --> 00:13:12.980
Anything you want to eat today?

00:13:15.024 --> 00:13:16.817
I haven't thought about it yet.

00:13:16.901 --> 00:13:20.821
You wanted lasagna last time.
I'll find a place that makes good lasagna.

00:13:20.905 --> 00:13:22.781
…I suspect that might be a trace of it.

00:13:22.865 --> 00:13:25.576
Like you said, it does have its strengths,

00:13:25.659 --> 00:13:28.287
but are they enough
to make up for the shortcomings--

00:13:28.370 --> 00:13:29.413
What are you doing?

00:13:37.129 --> 00:13:37.963
Why do you ask?

00:13:40.424 --> 00:13:41.342
It's nothing.

00:13:43.510 --> 00:13:44.637
Please continue.

00:13:47.431 --> 00:13:48.390
Eun-ho!

00:13:52.478 --> 00:13:53.729
Am I late?

00:13:53.812 --> 00:13:54.647
You're pretty.

00:14:08.535 --> 00:14:11.872
The few hours of freedom I have
after getting off work.

00:14:17.294 --> 00:14:20.214
I've finally found the perfect way

00:14:21.048 --> 00:14:22.466
to spend that time.

00:14:25.094 --> 00:14:25.970
Look at this one.

00:14:57.084 --> 00:15:00.754
Have I ever been on
such a perfect date before?

00:15:02.339 --> 00:15:03.924
This is so nice.

00:15:18.522 --> 00:15:21.358
Has time ever flown by so fast?

00:16:24.588 --> 00:16:25.631
Stop crying, okay?

00:16:32.346 --> 00:16:33.180
Hey.

00:16:34.431 --> 00:16:37.768
Drink this and forget about it,
or go beg him to take you back.

00:16:45.609 --> 00:16:48.320
There's none. They simply don't exist.

00:16:49.613 --> 00:16:50.697
What do you mean?

00:16:51.532 --> 00:16:54.618
No man in this world
is a perfect match for me.

00:16:55.160 --> 00:16:59.998
If I can't find one after meeting 30 guys,
that means no such man exists.

00:17:01.792 --> 00:17:03.710
Then what, are you gonna stop dating?

00:17:03.794 --> 00:17:06.046
I don't know. Fuck!

00:17:09.007 --> 00:17:10.843
Why are you suddenly swearing?

00:17:11.426 --> 00:17:12.886
It was all a waste!

00:17:12.970 --> 00:17:15.139
If I had put all that time
into something else,

00:17:15.222 --> 00:17:18.809
I wouldn't be worn out dealing with kids,
even with a master's degree.

00:17:18.892 --> 00:17:20.686
I would've made something of myself!

00:17:21.812 --> 00:17:24.898
Hey, don't be so dramatic.
It's not too late.

00:17:25.399 --> 00:17:26.900
It's hopeless.

00:17:27.985 --> 00:17:30.654
I've had all my energy drained by guys.

00:17:30.737 --> 00:17:32.948
Now I don't have the strength
to do anything.

00:17:34.575 --> 00:17:35.409
Hey.

00:17:37.911 --> 00:17:40.664
You have it better than me.

00:17:41.415 --> 00:17:42.666
I should have

00:17:43.333 --> 00:17:46.670
just lived like you!

00:17:53.844 --> 00:17:54.678
What?

00:17:59.600 --> 00:18:00.642
JI-YEON

00:18:00.726 --> 00:18:03.020
Hey, how's my profile picture?

00:18:03.103 --> 00:18:04.897
Can you tell I'm pretending to be okay?

00:18:06.857 --> 00:18:08.108
So obvious.

00:18:08.609 --> 00:18:10.944
EUN-HO

00:18:12.070 --> 00:18:13.030
Hello.

00:18:13.113 --> 00:18:15.407
Are you on your way?
What's up with your friend?

00:18:16.200 --> 00:18:17.910
She broke up with her boyfriend.

00:18:19.411 --> 00:18:20.829
That sounds rough.

00:18:21.413 --> 00:18:22.497
Hey, Eun-ho.

00:18:22.581 --> 00:18:26.251
Do you think there's a perfect match
for us somewhere in this world?

00:18:26.335 --> 00:18:28.587
Not sure. Why do you ask?

00:18:29.087 --> 00:18:30.547
Just curious.

00:18:30.631 --> 00:18:34.092
I guess I'm not good enough for you
if you're asking that.

00:18:35.385 --> 00:18:36.511
It's not like that.

00:18:38.472 --> 00:18:40.474
The weather's gotten really cold now.

00:18:41.391 --> 00:18:45.312
Had I found the answer
that Ji-yeon couldn't?

00:18:53.695 --> 00:18:55.113
-Eun-ho.
-Yes?

00:18:55.614 --> 00:18:59.368
When you're with me, do you enjoy it?

00:19:03.163 --> 00:19:05.082
First the call, and now this.

00:19:06.208 --> 00:19:07.834
That's an odd question to ask.

00:19:07.918 --> 00:19:10.754
Tell me. Do you really enjoy
being with me?

00:19:15.175 --> 00:19:16.426
What are you really asking?

00:19:22.474 --> 00:19:24.059
Our relationship…

00:19:26.061 --> 00:19:27.437
is a good thing, right?

00:19:28.438 --> 00:19:30.274
Is being with you

00:19:31.149 --> 00:19:32.734
the right choice for me?

00:19:36.113 --> 00:19:36.947
Mi-rae.

00:19:40.284 --> 00:19:42.369
When I'm with you, I'm so happy.

00:19:44.371 --> 00:19:46.123
And when I'm not with you,

00:19:47.457 --> 00:19:49.209
thinking about you makes me happy.

00:19:53.630 --> 00:19:55.382
What do you think of?

00:19:57.301 --> 00:19:58.343
The way you smile.

00:19:59.720 --> 00:20:01.138
The way you walk.

00:20:01.722 --> 00:20:02.806
The way you eat.

00:20:03.640 --> 00:20:05.058
The way you talk. Everything.

00:20:08.020 --> 00:20:09.021
So,

00:20:10.063 --> 00:20:11.315
put your doubts aside.

00:20:14.484 --> 00:20:15.319
Okay.

00:20:17.029 --> 00:20:18.071
I'm hurt, you know.

00:20:19.781 --> 00:20:20.615
Sorry.

00:20:28.582 --> 00:20:30.250
Ji-yeon couldn't find her answer.

00:20:33.670 --> 00:20:35.422
But I think I've found mine.

00:20:44.806 --> 00:20:47.392
Why would you eat with us?
Where's your team?

00:20:48.435 --> 00:20:51.938
They all wanted to go eat sushi,
and I can't eat uncooked food.

00:20:53.523 --> 00:20:56.109
I'm glad you're here.
You are always welcome to join us.

00:20:58.278 --> 00:21:00.864
Hey, you're all gonna attend
the workshop, aren't you?

00:21:01.948 --> 00:21:03.241
Workshop?

00:21:03.742 --> 00:21:05.660
-Yes, it's this week.
-You're not going?

00:21:06.995 --> 00:21:08.121
I'm not gonna go.

00:21:08.622 --> 00:21:09.623
I don't want to.

00:21:10.707 --> 00:21:11.792
Do I have to go?

00:21:13.710 --> 00:21:17.047
Don't you remember what happened
two years ago when you didn't go?

00:21:17.130 --> 00:21:17.964
Huh?

00:21:20.467 --> 00:21:22.260
Come on, it's barbecue time!

00:21:22.344 --> 00:21:24.846
-Barbecue!
-Mi-rae, it's barbecue!

00:21:24.930 --> 00:21:26.932
-Get in!
-Come on, Mi-rae!

00:21:36.358 --> 00:21:37.442
It's packed.

00:21:39.152 --> 00:21:40.028
I'm full.

00:21:41.863 --> 00:21:45.784
It's too much for one person to take on.
Are you sure she'll be okay?

00:21:45.867 --> 00:21:49.037
The authors have said yes,
so we can proceed as scheduled, but--

00:21:49.121 --> 00:21:51.498
-Let us know if you need help.
-Then it's settled.

00:21:51.581 --> 00:21:53.500
Sir, can you take a look at--

00:21:53.583 --> 00:21:55.085
-Anything else to add?
-No.

00:21:55.168 --> 00:21:56.002
Meeting adjourned.

00:21:59.423 --> 00:22:03.343
Hey, are you eating? Eat your fill.
Pretend that I'm paying for it.

00:22:05.846 --> 00:22:08.640
Sir, during the last workshop,
I had a stomach bug--

00:22:08.723 --> 00:22:10.559
Dong-min, order one stomach bug for…

00:22:12.519 --> 00:22:15.313
Get us one aged rib, man!

00:22:16.022 --> 00:22:17.607
Mi-rae, you're still here?

00:22:18.733 --> 00:22:20.068
First time seeing you here.

00:22:20.152 --> 00:22:23.572
The last workshop was amazing.
Workshops are the reason I haven't quit.

00:22:23.655 --> 00:22:25.907
That went on for three weeks.

00:22:25.991 --> 00:22:28.285
Hwang Byeong-hak is impossible
when he gets sulky.

00:22:28.368 --> 00:22:32.372
He's two years older now, so this time,
I think we're looking at six weeks.

00:22:34.249 --> 00:22:36.293
Kyeong-nam,
you didn't go back then either.

00:22:36.376 --> 00:22:37.711
Were you okay?

00:22:37.794 --> 00:22:39.838
Yes. I was okay.

00:22:39.921 --> 00:22:42.132
You're not going, are you?

00:22:43.175 --> 00:22:44.551
You're going, aren't you?

00:22:45.427 --> 00:22:48.096
Well, it'd be awkward
if I were the only one not going.

00:22:49.347 --> 00:22:50.265
I'm going.

00:22:50.849 --> 00:22:53.518
You're going to attend a two-day workshop?

00:22:53.602 --> 00:22:55.937
What's gotten into you? Are you bored?

00:22:56.021 --> 00:22:56.980
No.

00:22:57.981 --> 00:23:01.359
My parents live nearby,
and I have to see them on Friday.

00:23:02.027 --> 00:23:05.447
But it's a weekend.
You should spend time with your family.

00:23:06.615 --> 00:23:07.782
I'll take care of it.

00:23:09.743 --> 00:23:11.786
FLAMING JJAMPPONG

00:23:17.834 --> 00:23:19.586
That devilish jerk.

00:23:20.086 --> 00:23:23.340
Wow, this is the scent of nature.

00:23:24.174 --> 00:23:25.967
Wake up! How long are you going to sleep?

00:23:26.051 --> 00:23:27.427
WORK ALL NIGHT! WORKSHOP ALL NIGHT!

00:23:27.511 --> 00:23:29.763
Hey, you guys aren't carrying much.

00:23:30.263 --> 00:23:32.057
Boys, come back down here.

00:23:32.140 --> 00:23:35.268
Have fun. I miss you.

00:23:43.026 --> 00:23:44.694
Okay. I'll be in touch.

00:23:55.330 --> 00:23:56.164
Hello.

00:23:56.790 --> 00:23:57.624
Hello.

00:24:01.753 --> 00:24:04.506
Eun-ju! Take a picture of me over here.

00:24:05.006 --> 00:24:06.550
NAEMO'S 7TH ULTIMATE GEEK CONTEST

00:24:06.633 --> 00:24:09.803
All right, this is an old tradition
at our company.

00:24:09.886 --> 00:24:11.846
Who's the real deal?
The ultimate geek contest!

00:24:15.892 --> 00:24:19.521
The winner will have
the special opportunity to choose

00:24:19.604 --> 00:24:24.401
from a variety of collectible items
brought by Director Hwang!

00:24:24.484 --> 00:24:26.653
Hey, these are all limited edition!

00:24:27.237 --> 00:24:29.364
No improvement at all.

00:24:29.447 --> 00:24:31.283
-Since last time?
-We do this every time.

00:24:31.366 --> 00:24:33.660
Now then, here's question number one.

00:24:33.743 --> 00:24:37.080
Listen to the following line from a comic,
and guess which comic it is.

00:24:37.163 --> 00:24:41.084
"I talked to a guy for the first time.
Am I about to get a boyfriend?"

00:24:43.753 --> 00:24:46.006
-Seo Mi-rae.
-Mi-rae was faster. The answer is?

00:24:46.089 --> 00:24:48.091
I Want to Hold Aono-kun so Badly
I Could Die?

00:24:48.174 --> 00:24:50.594
-Correct!
-Really?

00:24:52.095 --> 00:24:53.179
Remember the name.

00:24:53.263 --> 00:24:55.515
-She's on Team 2.
-Question number two.

00:24:55.599 --> 00:24:56.641
Bringing up a classic.

00:24:56.725 --> 00:24:58.351
In Dragon Ball,

00:24:58.435 --> 00:25:01.605
which World Martial Arts Tournament
did Tenshinhan first appear in?

00:25:01.688 --> 00:25:02.689
Hye-bin!

00:25:03.815 --> 00:25:04.649
The 37th!

00:25:04.733 --> 00:25:05.609
Wrong.

00:25:05.692 --> 00:25:07.777
Mi-rae. The 23rd?

00:25:07.861 --> 00:25:09.863
-Wrong!
-It's over the 30th.

00:25:09.946 --> 00:25:10.947
No, it's not.

00:25:11.448 --> 00:25:13.033
-Kyeong-nam.
-Yes?

00:25:13.116 --> 00:25:15.827
-The 22nd.
-The 22nd?

00:25:15.910 --> 00:25:17.537
Correct!

00:25:21.291 --> 00:25:22.125
Kyeong-nam!

00:25:22.208 --> 00:25:24.878
In Polar Night, Cha Dong-hwan
served in the air force for--

00:25:24.961 --> 00:25:26.755
-Seo Mi-rae!
-Jesus.

00:25:26.838 --> 00:25:27.922
-Yes?
-Eight years.

00:25:28.006 --> 00:25:29.966
Eight years, correct!

00:25:30.467 --> 00:25:32.969
In Villain to Kill,
when Kwon Yu-ri is in danger,

00:25:33.053 --> 00:25:34.638
the hotelier helps her and says…

00:25:34.721 --> 00:25:36.222
-Park Kyeong-nam.
-Yes?

00:25:36.306 --> 00:25:37.307
"Good morning."

00:25:37.390 --> 00:25:38.642
Ding ding ding!

00:25:38.725 --> 00:25:41.061
In A Bona Fide Killer,
Bona's child carries around--

00:25:41.144 --> 00:25:42.020
Kyeong-nam.

00:25:42.103 --> 00:25:43.647
-Yes?
-Kongdoli.

00:25:43.730 --> 00:25:44.648
Correct!

00:25:44.731 --> 00:25:46.316
In Theme Park of Death, Baek Jin--

00:25:46.399 --> 00:25:47.651
-Seo Mi-rae!
-Yes?

00:25:47.734 --> 00:25:48.735
Rolling Z Train.

00:25:48.818 --> 00:25:50.070
Rolling Z Train, correct!

00:25:50.153 --> 00:25:51.488
Yup. She got that one right.

00:25:51.571 --> 00:25:54.574
In Transfer Student at Apocalypse High,
Geon-u's friend's sister--

00:25:54.658 --> 00:25:55.742
Kyeong-nam.

00:25:55.825 --> 00:25:57.494
-Class 2-5.
-Correct!

00:25:57.994 --> 00:26:00.997
In Abandoned House Diary, how tall
is Oh Seong-chan, who keeps passing out?

00:26:01.081 --> 00:26:02.207
Mi-rae.

00:26:02.290 --> 00:26:03.375
175 cm?

00:26:03.958 --> 00:26:05.168
-Wrong!
-Kyeong-nam.

00:26:06.836 --> 00:26:08.004
176.

00:26:08.755 --> 00:26:10.256
Correct!

00:26:12.384 --> 00:26:13.301
-Mi-rae.
-Kyeong-nam.

00:26:13.385 --> 00:26:14.302
-Mi-rae!
-Kyeong-nam.

00:26:14.386 --> 00:26:15.887
Seo Mi-rae, Arapra Garatus!

00:26:15.970 --> 00:26:18.181
Arapra Garatus, correct!

00:26:18.264 --> 00:26:20.183
That's it! Arapra Garatus!

00:26:21.226 --> 00:26:24.062
Our very own Seo Mi-rae
got the last question right.

00:26:24.145 --> 00:26:27.023
It was a nail-biter,
with both participants evenly matched!

00:26:27.107 --> 00:26:29.567
Now, I will be announcing the results.

00:26:29.651 --> 00:26:34.656
Naemo's 7th Ultimate Geek Contest 2025.
And the winner is…

00:26:40.245 --> 00:26:42.414
Park Kyeong-nam!

00:26:44.165 --> 00:26:48.002
Go Team 1! Go Park Kyeong-nam!

00:26:51.965 --> 00:26:55.552
Ms. Seo, which prize do you want
to find the most in the treasure hunt?

00:26:58.012 --> 00:26:59.180
An early leave.

00:27:02.434 --> 00:27:03.309
I'm so cold!

00:27:03.393 --> 00:27:05.228
I can't keep looking.

00:27:05.311 --> 00:27:08.231
Who even hides treasures in a stream
when it's this cold?

00:27:08.314 --> 00:27:09.482
A centipede!

00:27:10.942 --> 00:27:12.444
-Where?
-Oh, it's not.

00:27:12.527 --> 00:27:13.945
-It's a twig.
-Hey, your phone!

00:27:14.028 --> 00:27:15.697
Oh no! It's going down the stream!

00:27:15.780 --> 00:27:17.073
Oh God, no!

00:27:17.157 --> 00:27:18.324
-What do we do?
-No!

00:27:18.408 --> 00:27:20.285
-What do we do?
-No!

00:27:22.370 --> 00:27:24.706
Dong-min!

00:27:34.340 --> 00:27:35.300
Holy!

00:27:35.800 --> 00:27:37.677
-I'll show you.
-Just get in there.

00:27:37.761 --> 00:27:39.888
-Hurry! It's over there!
-Hold on a sec.

00:27:39.971 --> 00:27:41.848
-Hurry up!
-Go after it!

00:28:26.142 --> 00:28:27.227
Thank you.

00:28:28.561 --> 00:28:29.395
Aren't you cold?

00:28:29.979 --> 00:28:32.565
It must have hit a rock.
The screen's cracked.

00:28:34.400 --> 00:28:37.278
You're right. I only just bought this!

00:28:37.362 --> 00:28:39.197
I'm going to change my pants.

00:28:43.243 --> 00:28:44.828
Well done, Kyeong-nam.

00:28:47.330 --> 00:28:49.999
Hey, are you okay?
That was a brand-new phone.

00:28:50.083 --> 00:28:52.502
Yes, I'm fine.

00:28:53.461 --> 00:28:54.504
I feel good.

00:28:54.587 --> 00:28:55.672
-Huh?
-Good.

00:28:58.091 --> 00:28:59.467
Okay, let's all drink!

00:28:59.551 --> 00:29:02.679
-Hey, any song requests?
-Cheers!

00:29:03.429 --> 00:29:05.348
Fine, I'll just take care of it.

00:29:07.642 --> 00:29:10.895
I never thought
you would be attending this workshop.

00:29:10.979 --> 00:29:14.566
Since your parents live nearby,
do they farm oriental melons?

00:29:14.649 --> 00:29:18.152
Park Kyeong-nam definitely has
the makings of a star.

00:29:20.697 --> 00:29:22.448
You can't be serious.

00:29:22.532 --> 00:29:23.366
You saw him.

00:29:23.449 --> 00:29:26.953
He went in without any hesitation
when everyone else was standing around.

00:29:27.996 --> 00:29:28.913
Then he just left.

00:29:29.414 --> 00:29:31.332
Women go crazy for that kind of thing.

00:29:31.833 --> 00:29:32.917
Have a drink.

00:29:40.049 --> 00:29:40.967
I'll go get soju.

00:29:41.050 --> 00:29:42.552
As I turned into the alleyway

00:29:42.635 --> 00:29:44.804
The alleyway

00:29:45.889 --> 00:29:50.226
My heart was pounding

00:29:50.310 --> 00:29:52.312
Was pounding

00:29:52.395 --> 00:29:55.356
Curtains draped

00:29:55.440 --> 00:29:57.483
Over your window…

00:30:03.740 --> 00:30:04.574
Ms. Seo.

00:30:05.325 --> 00:30:06.159
Yes?

00:30:09.370 --> 00:30:10.204
What?

00:30:11.998 --> 00:30:12.874
Is that water?

00:30:15.001 --> 00:30:15.835
This?

00:30:16.586 --> 00:30:17.503
It's soju.

00:30:19.172 --> 00:30:21.174
Oh, it's soju.

00:30:22.550 --> 00:30:23.927
Soju's not good though.

00:30:25.011 --> 00:30:25.845
Huh?

00:30:26.512 --> 00:30:28.348
Soju is not good.

00:30:36.397 --> 00:30:39.859
This is also soju. The water's over there.

00:30:42.362 --> 00:30:43.529
Thank you.

00:30:50.328 --> 00:30:52.997
Seriously? He's a lightweight?

00:30:55.875 --> 00:30:56.709
Hot!

00:31:20.566 --> 00:31:22.318
Why don't these match?

00:31:28.199 --> 00:31:30.326
The bottles and lids don't match.

00:31:30.910 --> 00:31:33.997
What are you, a matchmaker?
Why are you trying to match them?

00:31:34.080 --> 00:31:37.625
No, it's this bottle.
It's supposed to have a matching lid.

00:31:39.752 --> 00:31:41.170
Hey. Look.

00:31:42.296 --> 00:31:43.840
-Over there.
-What in the world?

00:31:43.923 --> 00:31:46.050
I mean, there has to be a lid.

00:31:46.134 --> 00:31:47.260
Hey, look!

00:31:47.343 --> 00:31:49.053
Eun-ju, look at that!

00:31:49.137 --> 00:31:51.681
This guy has a weird habit
when he's drunk.

00:31:52.181 --> 00:31:54.058
Kyeong-nam. Let's get you to bed.

00:31:56.144 --> 00:31:58.479
You don't get it. It needs to have a lid.

00:31:58.563 --> 00:32:00.356
Yes, it does. God, you're heavy.

00:32:00.440 --> 00:32:03.693
-We're seeing so many new sides of him.
-This is important.

00:32:03.776 --> 00:32:05.194
Here. Careful.

00:32:05.278 --> 00:32:08.364
Did you hear what I said?
Without a lid, something bad will happen.

00:32:08.448 --> 00:32:10.908
-Sure, that's important.
-I'm serious.

00:32:10.992 --> 00:32:12.702
Sleep, okay? Sleep.

00:32:14.120 --> 00:32:17.040
-Hey, you guys. Sing a song.
-It really needs a lid.

00:32:17.123 --> 00:32:18.374
-Sing a song.
-I'm okay.

00:32:18.458 --> 00:32:20.376
-Well…
-Don't pick it up.

00:32:20.877 --> 00:32:24.964
Sing a song!

00:32:25.048 --> 00:32:26.507
Go on. Sing a song now.

00:32:26.591 --> 00:32:28.217
-I really can't--
-Do it!

00:32:28.885 --> 00:32:33.806
But after a long while

00:32:34.390 --> 00:32:39.062
I was crying on my own

00:32:39.145 --> 00:32:41.147
Feeling the pain

00:32:41.230 --> 00:32:45.735
I once caused you
Would you…

00:32:48.237 --> 00:32:49.238
The end.

00:32:51.532 --> 00:32:53.534
I didn't know this song was so short.

00:32:54.327 --> 00:32:55.536
Kyeong-nam's awake.

00:32:55.620 --> 00:32:58.039
Feel better? You can go back to sleep.

00:32:58.122 --> 00:32:59.207
I'm good.

00:32:59.957 --> 00:33:01.042
My ears were hurting.

00:33:01.125 --> 00:33:02.126
Your ears?

00:33:03.127 --> 00:33:05.379
-What on earth is he on about?
-His ears?

00:33:05.463 --> 00:33:06.714
Hey, your turn.

00:33:50.216 --> 00:33:52.677
I told her not to date
someone from the office.

00:33:56.764 --> 00:33:59.475
Mi-rae, aren't you glad you came?
Wasn't it so much fun?

00:33:59.559 --> 00:34:02.478
Director Hwang,
that was the best workshop of my life.

00:34:02.979 --> 00:34:05.481
-Don't skip these from now on.
-Of course I won't.

00:34:05.565 --> 00:34:08.359
-Guys, wasn't that fun?
-Let's go in Kyeong-nam's car.

00:34:09.110 --> 00:34:10.486
Dong-min!

00:34:10.570 --> 00:34:13.447
We'll take the bus.
Please take Eun-ju home safely.

00:34:13.531 --> 00:34:14.699
You can go in my car.

00:34:14.782 --> 00:34:17.702
Yes! It'll be more comfortable.
He's okay with it.

00:34:19.287 --> 00:34:20.454
-Come on!
-What?

00:34:21.164 --> 00:34:23.499
-Get in.
-Hurry up!

00:34:27.753 --> 00:34:29.422
I think I'll sit in the back.

00:34:29.505 --> 00:34:30.339
What?

00:34:37.305 --> 00:34:38.139
You getting in?

00:34:41.601 --> 00:34:42.768
Yes. Okay.

00:34:59.702 --> 00:35:01.037
You can drop me off here.

00:35:01.120 --> 00:35:03.039
I'll get out here too.

00:35:05.499 --> 00:35:07.168
Whoa, don't throw up in the car.

00:35:07.752 --> 00:35:10.087
Get out of the car. Hurry!

00:35:12.340 --> 00:35:13.591
I'll get out here too.

00:35:13.674 --> 00:35:14.717
You don't live here.

00:35:14.800 --> 00:35:16.761
I can take the subway. Thank you.

00:35:16.844 --> 00:35:19.013
I'll drive you.
I'm headed that way anyway.

00:35:24.560 --> 00:35:27.063
Get home safe. Kyeong-nam, thank you.

00:35:27.146 --> 00:35:28.731
See you tomorrow.

00:35:39.951 --> 00:35:42.203
Your diffuser has a really nice scent.

00:35:44.121 --> 00:35:44.956
Just shut up.

00:35:45.039 --> 00:35:47.416
I can smell alcohol on you.
You must've had too much.

00:35:47.500 --> 00:35:48.501
What?

00:35:49.585 --> 00:35:52.171
I didn't though. Did I?

00:35:55.424 --> 00:35:57.510
Can I drop you off near Yongsan Station?

00:35:57.593 --> 00:35:58.427
Yes.

00:35:59.095 --> 00:36:01.597
But don't you live in Seongsu?

00:36:02.098 --> 00:36:02.932
I do.

00:36:03.724 --> 00:36:04.558
Then why…

00:36:04.642 --> 00:36:06.894
I have a meeting with Hwany there.

00:36:07.895 --> 00:36:08.813
On a Sunday?

00:36:09.605 --> 00:36:10.439
Yes.

00:36:12.275 --> 00:36:14.568
I thought you really cared about
work-life balance.

00:36:14.652 --> 00:36:18.114
I don't want to get in the way
while he's trying to step up his game.

00:36:20.324 --> 00:36:23.452
He's trying to step up his game?

00:36:23.536 --> 00:36:24.745
I see.

00:36:25.246 --> 00:36:28.749
How's Ms. Yun doing?
Mr. Hwang seemed worried about her.

00:36:30.418 --> 00:36:31.502
Worried about what?

00:36:31.585 --> 00:36:34.505
Sales, probably.
They dropped a lot last month, after all.

00:36:35.756 --> 00:36:39.010
That was just a temporary dip
due to the coin event and her break.

00:36:39.093 --> 00:36:42.763
That, and her title has low ratings,
so I suppose it's making him nervous.

00:36:44.807 --> 00:36:45.641
I see.

00:36:45.725 --> 00:36:48.728
Having said that, it looks like
Hwany will be doing the short story

00:36:48.811 --> 00:36:51.814
that Ms. Yun was supposed to work on,
at the advertiser's request.

00:36:54.567 --> 00:36:56.152
Can I drop you off right there?

00:36:56.736 --> 00:36:57.570
Yes.

00:36:58.738 --> 00:37:03.367
Why does Mr. Hwang keep talking to you
instead of telling me himself?

00:37:03.993 --> 00:37:04.827
Who knows?

00:37:07.955 --> 00:37:09.373
Thank you for the ride.

00:37:10.666 --> 00:37:12.918
You don't have anything else to tell me?

00:37:15.921 --> 00:37:16.839
I do.

00:37:19.884 --> 00:37:20.718
What is it?

00:37:25.890 --> 00:37:27.308
I like you.

00:37:43.699 --> 00:37:44.533
What?

00:37:47.620 --> 00:37:48.496
What did you say?

00:37:48.579 --> 00:37:49.622
You heard me.

00:37:50.206 --> 00:37:53.334
No, I don't think so.

00:37:53.417 --> 00:37:55.586
I might have misheard you.

00:37:55.669 --> 00:37:57.046
I said

00:37:58.047 --> 00:37:59.715
I like you, Ms. Seo.

00:38:01.217 --> 00:38:04.595
What? I mean, where is this coming from?

00:38:07.640 --> 00:38:08.641
I should get going.

00:38:10.601 --> 00:38:11.435
See you tomorrow.

00:38:23.531 --> 00:38:26.158
What is he saying?

00:38:37.586 --> 00:38:38.546
Seriously.

00:38:39.505 --> 00:38:41.048
Is he actually crazy?

00:38:41.757 --> 00:38:43.759
He's messing with me, right?

00:38:44.969 --> 00:38:46.554
Wait, besides…

00:38:47.388 --> 00:38:49.181
I saw him with Eun-ju last night.

00:38:51.892 --> 00:38:53.102
That bastard!

00:38:53.686 --> 00:38:55.521
Is he trying to date two girls at work?

00:38:55.604 --> 00:38:56.856
I got rejected.

00:38:56.939 --> 00:38:59.233
At first, I was just fangirling over him.

00:38:59.316 --> 00:39:01.610
But it was late into the night,
I had a buzz going,

00:39:01.694 --> 00:39:04.071
and he was right next to me,
so I just took a shot.

00:39:04.155 --> 00:39:05.030
And?

00:39:05.114 --> 00:39:06.407
He shot me down coldly.

00:39:07.199 --> 00:39:09.118
I actually felt shot down.

00:39:10.494 --> 00:39:13.247
So, do I just need to be aware of this?

00:39:14.498 --> 00:39:16.041
Why don't you give it a thought?

00:39:16.125 --> 00:39:18.836
About dating me, that is.

00:39:19.420 --> 00:39:20.713
I don't think I can do that.

00:39:21.297 --> 00:39:22.381
Do you not like me?

00:39:25.301 --> 00:39:27.219
I don't particularly dislike you,

00:39:27.303 --> 00:39:29.305
but I don't think
I'll ever come to like you.

00:39:34.602 --> 00:39:37.688
Just a moment. Oh, my head…

00:39:40.524 --> 00:39:43.652
Wow, he really is just built differently.

00:39:44.153 --> 00:39:47.364
My phone broke, and my heart broke.
It was the worst workshop ever.

00:39:48.324 --> 00:39:49.575
What?

00:39:49.658 --> 00:39:52.620
So he actually meant what he told me?

00:39:56.665 --> 00:39:57.917
-Cover me!
-What?

00:39:58.000 --> 00:39:59.418
Why? What is it?

00:40:01.629 --> 00:40:03.714
Why?

00:40:03.797 --> 00:40:05.174
Why?

00:40:05.257 --> 00:40:07.676
Why?

00:40:07.760 --> 00:40:08.886
What are you doing?

00:40:10.930 --> 00:40:12.264
Are you playing trains?

00:40:12.348 --> 00:40:14.517
-I wanna play too!
-Off we go!

00:40:20.022 --> 00:40:21.649
Let's get back to work.

00:40:23.609 --> 00:40:24.777
I like it.

00:40:28.572 --> 00:40:30.741
The readers would really like this part.

00:40:30.824 --> 00:40:34.578
I liked the witty homage in the beginning,
and I also liked the art style.

00:40:35.079 --> 00:40:38.040
It doesn't follow the trend,
but it has a rookie's originality.

00:40:38.123 --> 00:40:41.210
In conclusion,
the readers will definitely like it.

00:40:41.293 --> 00:40:43.629
I like you.

00:40:44.129 --> 00:40:46.549
Get a grip!

00:40:47.174 --> 00:40:49.260
-Take a short break?
-Sure.

00:40:57.309 --> 00:40:58.352
Me too.

00:41:04.567 --> 00:41:05.568
Push.

00:41:20.207 --> 00:41:22.126
This is driving me crazy.

00:41:33.095 --> 00:41:34.680
We're not meeting today either?

00:41:36.348 --> 00:41:39.018
See you later. I'll leave work early.

00:41:52.823 --> 00:41:53.782
Ms. Seo.

00:41:53.866 --> 00:41:54.700
Yes?

00:41:55.367 --> 00:41:56.619
Did I make a mistake?

00:41:58.037 --> 00:41:58.871
Sorry?

00:42:05.753 --> 00:42:07.129
I didn't think you'd avoid me.

00:42:07.212 --> 00:42:10.799
Me? Avoid you? When did I ever…

00:42:11.634 --> 00:42:12.718
Can I wait

00:42:13.552 --> 00:42:14.511
for your answer?

00:42:15.471 --> 00:42:16.722
Oh God…

00:42:17.222 --> 00:42:18.057
Or

00:42:19.058 --> 00:42:20.100
should I just give up?

00:42:27.650 --> 00:42:29.652
Well, you know, I--

00:42:29.735 --> 00:42:33.113
If you're seeing someone,
you can just tell me.

